<p class="">Plain text:</p><p class="">Oct. 16, 10am-1pm</p><p class="">Join us in caring for the land of the Pine Street Barge Canal.</p><p class="">Following up on the work of Green Up Day 2022, we’ll remove trash from the Barge Canal, helping this damaged but beautiful land along Lake Champlain continue the quiet task of healing itself.</p><p class="">Come for an hour or stay the whole time.</p><p class="">Rain or shine. Wear sturdy shoes, socks and long pants. Bring work gloves if you have them; we also have some to borrow. Bring water to drink, snacks if needed.</p><p class="">Look for the red umbrella across Pine Street from Dealer Dot Com.</p><p class="">Questions? Please write to Friends of the Barge Canal, <a href="mailto:sosburlington@gmail.com">sosburlington@gmail.com </a></p>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/jpeg" url="../images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/632919d9c05fec09f1a64f78/1664808717131-H1WL957UQFU5QGBN2QFP/Rubydraggingbrush.jpg?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1875"><media:title type="plain">October 16th: Fall Clean Up Day!</media:title></media:content></item></channel></rss>